# Swiper Standards

This project uses **Swiper 12.x** via a global `window.Swiper` (registered from `src/js/swiper-init.js`). Modules (Navigation, Pagination, Autoplay, FreeMode, Scrollbar, A11y, EffectFade, Thumbs) are registered globally via `Swiper.use([...])` — no per-block module imports needed. Call `new Swiper(...)` directly.

Block SCSS rules are always nested inside an outer `.{slug}-section` wrapper; child classes are plain (`.slide`, `.controls`, `.card`) — no BEM `__` prefixes. Uniqueness comes from nesting, not prefixes.

---

## 1. HTML Structure (PHP partial)

```php
<section class="{slug}-section section">
	<div class="container">
		<!-- Slider -->
		<div class="{slug}-slider swiper">
			<div class="swiper-wrapper">
				<div class="slide swiper-slide">
					<!-- slide content -->
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Controls (outside .swiper so they aren't clipped by overflow:hidden) -->
		<div class="controls">
			<!-- Add swiper-pagination-line for bar shape; directional animation is automatic if the CSS hook exists (see §4) -->
			<div class="swiper-pagination swiper-pagination-line"></div>
			<div class="swiper-navigation">
				<button type="button" class="swiper-button-prev" aria-label="Previous slide">
					<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
						<path d="M19 12H5M11 18l-6-6 6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
					</svg>
				</button>
				<button type="button" class="swiper-button-next" aria-label="Next slide">
					<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
						<path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
					</svg>
				</button>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
```

### Key points

- The slider container gets **two classes**: `{slug}-slider` (JS hook) and `swiper` (Swiper core).
- Each slide gets **two classes**: `slide` (styling — scoped by nesting inside `.{slug}-section`) and `swiper-slide` (Swiper core).
- Child class names are **plain** (`.slide`, `.controls`, `.card`) — not BEM (`{slug}__slide`). Uniqueness comes from nesting inside `.{slug}-section` in SCSS.
- Navigation/pagination elements sit **outside** the `.swiper` wrapper to avoid `overflow: hidden` clipping.
- Navigation wrapper is always `.swiper-navigation` — **never** use block-specific nav wrapper classes.
- Navigation buttons are always `.swiper-button-prev` and `.swiper-button-next` — **never** use block-specific button classes.
- Buttons are `<button type="button">` with `aria-label`.
- SVG icons use `aria-hidden="true"` and `stroke="currentColor"`.

