## 4. SCSS Rules

### Slide sizing

Use `slidesPerView: 'auto'` in JS and set slide width via SCSS (all rules nested inside `.{slug}-section`):

```scss
.{slug}-section {
	.slide {
		inline-size: fluid(280, 400);  // responsive slide width
		max-inline-size: 95%;
	}
}
```

### Flex/grid parent fix

If the `.swiper` sits inside a flex or grid container, add:

```scss
.{slug}-section {
	.{slug}-slider {
		min-inline-size: 0;
	}
}
```

Without this, `min-inline-size: auto` prevents the slider from shrinking and breaks scrolling.

### Navigation styling

Global navigation styles live in `src/sass/partials/template-parts/_swiper-navigation.scss`. Wrap nav buttons in a `.swiper-navigation` container to inherit these styles:

- 44×44px circular buttons, `all: unset` base
- Disabled state: `opacity: 0.5; pointer-events: none`
- Hover micro-animations on SVG arrows (`micro-left` / `micro-right` keyframes)
- Style variants: `.style-floating` (absolute positioned), `.style-dark` (dark background)

### Pagination styling

Global pagination styles live in `src/sass/partials/js-plugins/_swiper-custom.scss`. Available classes:

| Class                    | Look                | Status                                 |
| ------------------------ | ------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| `swiper-pagination-dot`  | Circular dots       | Present in `_swiper-custom.scss`       |
| `swiper-scrollbar`       | Draggable scrollbar | Present in `_swiper-custom.scss`       |
| `swiper-pagination-line` | Equal-width bars    | **Not yet defined globally** — see note |

> **Note:** `swiper-pagination-line` and the automatic directional-fill animation described below are the conventions for this project but **have not yet been added to `_swiper-custom.scss`**. The JS `snapIndexChange` handler still works (it only sets `data-direction`), but the visual fill won't render until the CSS hook is added globally. Until then, either add the styling in the block's own SCSS or extend `_swiper-custom.scss` separately. Keep block-specific tweaks in the block file; promote shared styling into the global partial when it stabilises.

### Directional animation (target behaviour)

Once the CSS hook exists in `_swiper-custom.scss`, forward/backward fill animation should be applied by default to `swiper-pagination-line`, `swiper-pagination-dot`, and `swiper-scrollbar`.

How it works:

- Forward swipe: active bullet fills **left → right**, previous bullet empties **right → left**
- Backward swipe: directions reverse
- The JS `snapIndexChange` handler sets `data-direction` on the pagination/scrollbar container (see §2)
- The handler is bound on the Swiper instance **after** init, not in the config `on` object
- The CSS reacts via attribute selectors like `.swiper-pagination[data-direction='forward'] .swiper-pagination-bullet-active::after { … }`

Color overrides — override per-block in the block's SCSS (nested inside `.{slug}-section`):

```scss
.{slug}-section {
	.swiper-pagination .swiper-pagination-bullet {
		background-color: $your-track-color;

		&::after {
			background-color: $your-fill-color;
		}
	}
}
```

### Custom overrides

Block-specific pagination/nav tweaks go in the block's own SCSS file, not in the global partials.

